response.Q0: Initially I tried different routes and totalled up the score as I went and as soon as I found a high end score and went with that route.
response.Q1: I worked out what was a good end score and just tested the outer nodes to find anything above 70. As soon as I found a high end node I went directly to that, rather than test lots of nods and potentially lose money on the way.
response.Q2: I found it easy to to improve my performance. On a few occasions I wasn't able to click the node in time and lost the option to test routes. This ended in a low score on those occasions.
